As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 853 people, 264 households, and 224 families residing in the town, up from 769 in 2000 and 790 at the [[2010 United States census|2010 census]].<ref name=":0" /> The racial and ethnic makeup of the town in 2000 was 72.43% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 18.73% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.26% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 6.50% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 2.08% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino Americans]] of any race were 9.10% of the population.<ref name="GR2" />

